TextEng: Let me ask you some questions first.
Me can ask question first?
<StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> I accept your surrender, if the other goblins stop fighting me.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 항복을 받아들이지. 다른 고블린들이 날 공격하지 않는다면.

TextEng: <StartCheck>[Persuade]</Start> Me says surrender okay, if no goblins is fighting me.
Text: <StartCheck>[설득]</Start> 나 항복 받아줘, 고블린들 나 안 공격하면.

TextEng: I can't accept your surrender unless I get something out of it.
Text: 뭔가 얻어야 항복을 받아들일 수 있어.

TextEng: Me listen to offer. Me gets something, yuh?
Text: 나 제안 들을게. 나 뭔가 얻어야 해, 알지?

TextEng: Actually, I enjoy killing goblins. No deal.
Text: 사실 난 고블린 죽이는 걸 즐겨. 거래 없어.

TextEng: Me likes goblin-killing too much. No deals!
Text: 나 고블린 죽이는 거 너무 좋아. 거래 없어!

TextEng: Then I guess I'll have to kill you.
Me can kill you then. No problems.
Bye.
Tell me about these caves.
Me wants knowing what goes on in cave.
Text: 나 동굴에서 무슨 일 있는지 알고 싶어.

TextEng: Where is your chieftain?
Where you chieftain is?
Master? Who's your master? Your chieftain?
You chieftain is master, yuh?
I need more than that if I'm not to kill you.
Text: 널 죽이지 않으려면 더 많은 정보가 필요해.

TextEng: Me needs more or me kills you.
Text: 나 더 알아야 해, 안 그러면 너 죽여.

TextEng: That's fine. I accept.
Me can accept that offer. Me okay.
